In the following example, only Foo produces `UNOPTFLAT` warning whereas `Bar` doesn't. I expected `Foo` and `Bar` are equivalent after V3SplitVar pass. 
```verilog
module Foo(
  input  a,
  output b);
  
  wire  [1:0] w /*verilator split_var*/;
  assign w = {w[0], a};
  assign b = w[1];
endmodule

module Bar(
  input  a,
  output b);
  
  wire  w_1, w_0;
  assign {w_1, w_0} = {w_0, a};
  assign b = w_1;
endmodule
```
Verilator 5.004 2022-12-14 rev v5.004
